Look up in allodb information about each equation_id.

Source: R/allo_lookup.R
allo_lookup.Rd

Look up in allodb information about each equation_id.

allo_lookup(.data, allodb = allodb::equations)

Arguments

.data

A dataframe with columns rowid and equation_id
allodb

A table from allodb.

Value

A dataframe.

See also

Other functions to manipulate equations: add_equations, evaluate_equations, get_equations, pick_best_equations

Examples

census <- allodb::scbi_tree1
species <- allodb::scbi_species

single_best <- census %>%
  census_species(species, site = "scbi") %>%
  get_equations() %>%
  pick_best_equations() %>%
  pick_one_row_by_rowid()

ids <- add_equations(census, single_best)
#> Joining, by = "rowid"
allo_lookup(ids)
